# Presentation Builder

## Slide contract (`src/types/slide.ts`)

**Deck types:** `project_status`, `executive_update`, `weekly_report`, `rollout_plan`, `project_kickoff`, `client_presentation`

**Layouts:** `title`, `bullets`, `metrics_grid`, `timeline`, `two_column`, `image_caption`, `chart`, `quote`, `section_break`

**Slide shape:**
```ts
{ id, order, type, layout, title, content: SlideContent, speakerNotes?, metadata? }
```

`SlideContent` fields by layout:
- `bullets` → `bullets: string[]`
- `metrics_grid` → `metrics: { label, value, trend? }[]`
- `chart` → `chartData: Record<string, string|number>[]`
- `image_caption` → `imageUrl`, `imageAlt`, `body?`
- `quote` → `quote`, `attribution?`
- default body text → `body`

## Outline → slides pipeline

1. AI produces `DeckOutline` (titles, layouts, summaries)
2. User approves outline → status `approved`
3. Inngest job fills `SlideContent` per slide → status `ready`

## Export (`lib/export/`)

- Use `pptxgenjs`; one PPTX slide per app slide
- Apply `brand_kits` (logo, primary/accent colors, font) when `apply_branding`
- Map each layout to a PPTX master layout template
- Upload result to `exports` bucket; update `exports` row

## Component rules

- `components/slides/` — one renderer per layout for preview
- Preview renderer and export mapper must share layout logic (extract to `lib/export/layouts/`)
- DnD reorder updates `order` field; persist batch on drop

## Validation

- Zod schema mirrors `Slide` / `DeckOutline` types
- Reject unknown layouts or deck types at API boundary
- Cap slides per deck (e.g., 40) to control AI cost
